parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to stalling, loss of power, and potentially causing accidents. It can also lead to costly repairs, leaving the driver stranded and without a vehicle.
symptoms: The engine overheats
coolant levels drop
white smoke or steam is emitted from the exhaust
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the check engine light comes on
and the engine runs rough.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight switch can cause the headlights to go out or flicker, leading to a loss of visibility, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or blink
headlights go out
smoke comes from the steering column
high beams do not work
low beams are dim or inoperable
fog lights stay on while headlights are off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the headlight wiring harness connector can cause the headlights to go out or flicker, leading to a loss of visibility, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Headlights flicker or blink
headlights go out
smoke comes from the steering column
high beams do not work
low beams are dim or inoperable
fog lights stay on while headlights are off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The deterioration of the headlight lens assembly can cause the headlights to be dim or inoperable, leading to a loss of visibility, which can increase the risk of a crash.
symptoms: Headlights are dim or inoperable
low beams are restricted
visibility is reduced at night.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure
the vehicle is unable to stop or has extended stopping distance.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate violently when braking, leading to loss of control or accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates when braking
the front end of the vehicle shakes
the brake pedal pulsates
the brake rotors are excessively worn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS motor can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The ABS motor engages unnecessarily
the brakes grab or lock up
the vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking
the ABS motor remains on after turning off the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brake pedal to stick to the floor, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal sticks to the floor
the brake pedal does not return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a delayed return to its normal position
the brake pedal has a sudden loss of pressure.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the head gasket can cause the engine to overheat, leading to engine damage or failure.
symptoms: White smoke comes from the exhaust pipe
the temperature gauge goes up
the engine uses excessive oil or coolant
the engine stalls or runs poorly.
